<subSubSection id="51F4652BFF8CD157FF41FD2F3E229E71" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph id="195136A0FF8CD157FF41FD2F3E229E71" blockId="3.[189,1398,761,893]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The species of this new subgenus can be recognized by the shape of the trochanter of fore and middle legs with a basal laminar projection (
<figureCitation id="81D52A25FF8CD157FD99FCCA3F809E3A" box="[613,680,796,822]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,950,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1396,950,1853]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Trochanter of female fore leg (ZMB †). A. Centris anisitsi (Schrottky, 1908), Paraguay, San Bernardino (LPBC †). B. C. hyptidis Ducke, 1908, Brazil, Vitória da Conquista (MNRJ †). C. C. hyptidoides Roig-Alsina, 2000, Paraguay, San Pedro Cororo (MNRJ †). D. C. thelyopsis Vivallo &amp; Melo, 2009, Brazil, Teresina de Goiás (DZUP †). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011108" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011108/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A–D), and by the fore elaiospathes of the females (
<figureCitation id="81D52A25FF8CD157FB0CFCCA381A9E3A" box="[1264,1330,796,822]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1896,1922]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,952,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[192,1396,952,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Elaiospathe of female fore leg. A. Centris anisitsi (Schrottky, 1908), Paraguay, San Bernardino (ZMB †). B. C. hyptidis Ducke, 1908, Brazil, Vitória da Conquista (MNRJ †). C.C. hyptidoides Roig- Alsina, 2000, Paraguay, San Pedro Cororo (LPBC †). D. C. thelyopsis Vivallo &amp; Melo, 2009, Brazil, Teresina de Goiás (DZUP †). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011110/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A–D) with extremely small posterior giant setae. This rudimentary secondary comb apparently is not used for oil collection, judging by their vestigial condition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="51F4652BFF8CD157FF41FC7239399991" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="195136A0FF8CD157FF41FC723C6C9EB2" blockId="3.[189,324,932,958]" box="[189,324,932,958]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="421981CCFF8CD157FF41FC723C6C9EB2" bold="true" box="[189,324,932,958]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FF41FC723C6C9EB2" bold="true" box="[189,324,932,958]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="195136A0FF8CD157FF41FC0539399991" blockId="3.[189,1399,979,1181]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
From Greek ‘ 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FEA2FC023C819EE1" box="[350,425,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">anisos</emphasis>
’ (‘unequal’) and ‘ 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FD7CFC053FCF9EE1" box="[640,743,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">ctenodes</emphasis>
’ (‘comb-like’) based on the particular shape of the fore elaiospathe of the females. The morphology of the oil-collecting apparatuses of the species of this group is unique in 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FEACFBCC3C8E9938" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1804" box="[336,422,1050,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FEACFBCC3C8E9938" box="[336,422,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Centris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which contrasts with the pattern found in the rest of the species of the genus. The shape considered ancestral includes an anterior primary comb formed by a single row of enlarged, flattened and apically curved overlapping setae, and a secondary comb formed by four giant spatulate setae located in opposition to the primary comb (
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8CD157FD06FB55392C9991" author="Neff J. L. &amp; Simpson B. B." box="[762,1028,1155,1181]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="95 - 123" refId="ref7607" refString="Neff J. L. &amp; Simpson B. B. 1981. Oil-collecting structures in the Anthophoridae (Hymenoptera): morphology, function and use in systematics. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society 54: 95 - 123." type="journal article" year="1981">Neff &amp; Simpson 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="51F4652BFF8CD157FF41FB123EA59801" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="195136A0FF8CD157FF41FB123CA499D2" blockId="3.[189,396,1220,1246]" box="[189,396,1220,1246]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="421981CCFF8CD157FF41FB123CA499D2" bold="true" box="[189,396,1220,1246]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FF41FB123CA499D2" bold="true" box="[189,396,1220,1246]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Species included</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="195136A0FF8CD157FF41FB253EA59801" blockId="3.[189,909,1267,1293]" box="[189,909,1267,1293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FF41FB253C589801" baseAuthorityName="Schrottky" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[189,368,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisitsi">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FF41FB253C589801" box="[189,368,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Centris anisitsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FE82FB253CD59801" box="[382,509,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptidis">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FE82FB253CD59801" box="[382,509,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C. hyptidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FDF0FB253F9D9801" authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="2000" box="[524,693,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptidoides">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FDF0FB253F9D9801" box="[524,693,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C. hyptidoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FD12FB253EAE9801" box="[750,902,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thelyopsis">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FD12FB253EAE9801" box="[750,902,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C. thelyopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="51F4652BFF8CD157FF41FAE23EC59B78" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="195136A0FF8CD157FF41FAE23C079842" blockId="3.[189,303,1332,1358]" box="[189,303,1332,1358]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="421981CCFF8CD157FF41FAE23C079842" bold="true" box="[189,303,1332,1358]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FF41FAE23C079842" bold="true" box="[189,303,1332,1358]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="195136A0FF8CD157FF41FAB53EC59B78" blockId="3.[189,1399,1379,1652]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Most species of 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FE7FFAB53F049871" authority="Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" box="[387,556,1379,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Anisoctenodes">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FE7FFAB53F049871" box="[387,556,1379,1405]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Anisoctenodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="30A957C9FF8CD157FDC9FAB53FE39871" box="[565,715,1379,1405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
exhibit interesting associations with oil-offering flowers, mainly with 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FEADFA503CE298AC" box="[337,458,1414,1440]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Angelonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FEADFA503CE298AC" box="[337,458,1414,1440]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Angelonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FE24FA503FA798AD" box="[472,655,1414,1441]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Plantaginaceae</taxonomicName>
). The species of this genus have trichomatic elaiophores, which require specialized structures for their exploitation (
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8CD157FCDBFA7F3E9C98CF" author="Vogel S." box="[807,948,1449,1475]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refId="ref8181" refString="Vogel S. 1974. Olblumen und ˆ lsammelnde Bienen. Tropische und Subtropische Pflanzenwelt 7. Steiner, Wiesbaden." type="book" year="1974">Vogel 1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8CD157FC3EFA7F39E798CF" author="Neff J. L. &amp; Simpson B. B." box="[962,1231,1449,1475]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="95 - 123" refId="ref7607" refString="Neff J. L. &amp; Simpson B. B. 1981. Oil-collecting structures in the Anthophoridae (Hymenoptera): morphology, function and use in systematics. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society 54: 95 - 123." type="journal article" year="1981">Neff &amp; Simpson 1981</bibRefCitation>
). The females have long and branched hairs of spatulate apex (
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8CD157FD05FA1A393398EA" author="Vogel S. &amp; Machado I. C." box="[761,1051,1484,1510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="153 - 178" refId="ref8202" refString="Vogel S. &amp; Machado I. C. 1991. Pollination of four sympatric species of Angelonia (Scrophulariaceae) by oil-collecting bees in NE, Brazil. Plant Systematics and Evolution 178: 153 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00937962" type="journal article" year="1991">Vogel &amp; Machado 1991</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 9C, G and 
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8CD157FB2BFA1A3DD49B06" author="Martins A. C. &amp; Aguiar A. J. C. &amp; Alves-dos-Santos I." pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref7227" refString="Martins A. C., Aguiar A. J. C. &amp; Alves-dos-Santos I. 2013. Interaction between oil-collecting bees and seven species of Plantaginaceae. Flora - Morphology Distribution Functional Ecology of Plants 208 (7): 1 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. flora. 2013.07.001" type="journal article" year="2013">
Martins 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FAC7FA1B385E98EA" box="[1339,1398,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 9C–E). These bristles are used for oil collection not through scraping by the elaiophores as in other species of 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FE86F9C53CF89B21" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1804" box="[378,464,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FE86F9C53CF89B21" box="[378,464,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Centris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but by absorption, using capillarity forces (
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8CD157FC2DF9C539C69B21" author="Vogel S. &amp; Machado I. C." box="[977,1262,1555,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="153 - 178" refId="ref8202" refString="Vogel S. &amp; Machado I. C. 1991. Pollination of four sympatric species of Angelonia (Scrophulariaceae) by oil-collecting bees in NE, Brazil. Plant Systematics and Evolution 178: 153 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00937962" type="journal article" year="1991">Vogel &amp; Machado 1991</bibRefCitation>
). A detailed description of the oil-collecting apparatus and the collecting behavior of 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FBD1F9E039879B5C" box="[1069,1199,1590,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptidis">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FBD1F9E039699B5C" box="[1069,1089,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FBAEF9E039879B5C" box="[1106,1199,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">hyptidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be found in 
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8CD157FF41F98F3CE99B7F" author="Machado I. C. &amp; Vogel S. &amp; Lopes A. V." box="[189,449,1625,1651]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="352 - 359" refId="ref7077" refString="Machado I. C., Vogel S. &amp; Lopes A. V. 2002. Pollination of Angelonia cornigera Hook (Scrophulariaceae) by long legged, oil-collecting bees in NE Brazil. Plant Biology 4: 352 - 359. https: // doi. org / 10.1055 / s- 2002 - 32325" type="journal article" year="2002">
Machado 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FECDF98C3C449B7F" box="[305,364,1625,1651]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
and in 
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8CD157FDE5F98F3E239B7F" author="Martins A. C. &amp; Aguiar A. J. C. &amp; Alves-dos-Santos I." box="[537,779,1625,1651]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref7227" refString="Martins A. C., Aguiar A. J. C. &amp; Alves-dos-Santos I. 2013. Interaction between oil-collecting bees and seven species of Plantaginaceae. Flora - Morphology Distribution Functional Ecology of Plants 208 (7): 1 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. flora. 2013.07.001" type="journal article" year="2013">
Martins 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FD87F98C3F9E9B7F" box="[635,694,1625,1651]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FCC0F98C3ECE9B7F" authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="2000" box="[828,998,1625,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptidoides">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FCC0F98C3E789B78" box="[828,848,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FCA3F98F3ECE9B7F" box="[863,998,1625,1651]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">hyptidoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
