<subSubSection id="51F4652BFF8CD150FF41F9633E849C60" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="195136A0FF8CD157FF41F9633C4C9BDE" blockId="3.[189,1399,1717,1992]" box="[189,356,1717,1746]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FF41F9633C4C9BDE" bold="true" box="[189,356,1717,1746]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="195136A0FF8CD157FF41F90C38109AC4" blockId="3.[189,1399,1717,1992]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The species of 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FE8BF90C3F089BF8" authority="Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" box="[375,544,1754,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Anisoctenodes">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FE8BF90C3F089BF8" box="[375,544,1754,1780]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Anisoctenodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="30A957C9FF8CD157FDD7F90C3FEA9BF9" box="[555,706,1754,1781]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
occur in the South American diagonal of open dry areas formed by the Caatinga, Cerrado, Chacoan and Pampean Provinces. These provinces belong to the Chacoan subregion of the Neotropics (
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8CD157FD6AF8F73E629A37" author="Morrone J. J." box="[662,842,1825,1851]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref7401" refString="Morrone J. J. 2014. Biogeographical regionalisation of the Neotropical Region. Zootaxa 3782 (1): 1 - 110. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3782.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Morrone 2014</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FC9DF8F739089A37" box="[865,1056,1825,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptidis">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FC9DF8F739089A37" box="[865,1056,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Centris hyptidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed mainly in the Caatinga, with peripheral records in the north of the 
<collectingRegion id="DB2AF842FF8CD157FCD5F8923E519A52" box="[809,889,1860,1886]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Paraná</collectingRegion>
Forest Province and in the Cerrado. In this latter province also occurs 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FE0BF8BE3FA69A8D" box="[503,654,1895,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thelyopsis">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FE0BF8BE3F239A8E" box="[503,523,1896,1922]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FDE5F8B13FA69A8D" box="[537,654,1895,1921]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">thelyopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the dry forests of the upper 
<collectingRegion id="DB2AF842FF8CD157FC08F8B1394E9A8D" box="[1012,1126,1895,1921]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
River (
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8CD157FB40F8B13DD59AA9" author="Vivallo F. &amp; Melo G. A. R." pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="33 - 44" refId="ref8074" refString="Vivallo F. &amp; Melo G. A. R. 2009. Taxonomy and geographic distribution of the species of Centris of the hyptidis group (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Centridini), with a description of a new species from Central Brazil. Zootaxa 2075: 33 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2075.1.2" type="journal article" year="2009">Vivallo &amp; Melo 2009</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FEF3F85D3CE89AA8" baseAuthorityName="Schrottky" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[271,448,1931,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisitsi">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FEF3F85D3CE89AA8" box="[271,448,1931,1957]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Centris anisitsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8CD157FE0AF85D3FB69AA8" authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="2000" box="[502,670,1930,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptidoides">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FE0AF85D3F229AA9" box="[502,522,1931,1957]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8CD157FDEBF85C3FB69AA8" box="[535,670,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">hyptidoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distributed in the Chacoan Province, with the latter species also being registered – for the moment by a single record – in the 
<collectingRegion id="DB2AF842FF8CD157FC3DF87839399AC4" box="[961,1041,1966,1992]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Paraná</collectingRegion>
Forest Province (
<figureCitation id="81D52A25FF8CD157FB1DF87838019AC4" box="[1249,1321,1966,1992]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,2000,2026]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,1100,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[190,1398,1057,1960]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 7. Distribution map of the species of Centris (Anisoctenodes) subgen. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011118/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="195136A0FF8BD150FF41FEDD3E849C60" blockId="4.[189,1398,267,364]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The description of the morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8BD150FD73FEDA3E659C29" box="[655,845,267,294]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptidis">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8BD150FD73FEDA3E659C29" box="[655,845,267,294]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Centris hyptidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8BD150FCA3FEDA39239C29" authorityName="Roig-Alsina" authorityYear="2000" box="[863,1035,267,294]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyptidoides">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8BD150FCA3FEDA3E5B9C2A" box="[863,883,268,294]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8BD150FC78FEDD39239C29" box="[900,1035,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">hyptidoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8BD150FBB6FEDA39CD9C29" box="[1098,1253,267,294]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thelyopsis">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8BD150FBB6FEDA39769C2A" box="[1098,1118,268,294]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8BD150FB8CFEDD39CD9C29" box="[1136,1253,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">thelyopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, along with their distribution ranges and floral hosts, can be found in 
<bibRefCitation id="7D7F4B51FF8BD150FC99FEF839539C45" author="Vivallo F. &amp; Melo G. A. R." box="[869,1147,302,329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="33 - 44" refId="ref8074" refString="Vivallo F. &amp; Melo G. A. R. 2009. Taxonomy and geographic distribution of the species of Centris of the hyptidis group (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Centridini), with a description of a new species from Central Brazil. Zootaxa 2075: 33 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2075.1.2" type="journal article" year="2009">Vivallo &amp; Melo (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. The redescription of 
<taxonomicName id="DEEE4D23FF8BD150FF41FE843C1C9C60" baseAuthorityName="Schrottky" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[189,308,338,364]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisitsi">
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8BD150FF41FE843DF99C60" box="[189,209,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="2B9AEAB2FF8BD150FF23FE853C1C9C60" box="[223,308,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">anisitsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the description of the female are provided below.
</paragraph>
